FBIS4-55441 "dreeu094_y_94009" FBIS-EEU-94-094 Daily Report 16 May 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Serbia Official Comments on Status of Refugees Official Comments on Status of Refugees LD1605103294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 0917 GMT 16 May 94 LD1605103294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Belgrade, 16 May (TANJUG) -- The revision of the refugee status has been completed in most of the municipalities in Serbia, Slobodan Popovic, Serbian deputy commissionaire for refugees, has told TANJUG. "Between 20 and 35 percent previously registered refugees have lost their status in the municipalities which have completed the revision." Many of them are already planning to return, in most cases after the school year ends. Most of the refugees will be returning to the Banjaluka, Bijeljina, and Baranja regions," Popovic says. The revision of the status has not been completed yet in Belgrade, Novi Sad, Sabac, Sombor, and Kragujevac, the municipalities with the largest number of registered refugees. The revision in these municipalities has been extended until the end of May. This process has been completed for between 25 and 30 percent of all refugees registered in Belgrade.
